        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 614 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Dallas Lake, or 13 miles southwest of Selmont-West Selmont, moving
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Belknap, Whites Bluff, Robert F. Henry Lock And Dam, Benton, Tyler,
Craig Field Aiport, Dallas Lake, Old Cahaba Park, White Hall, Selma
Drag Strip, Collirene, Mosses, and Dannelly Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
